<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1324,284,990]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,412,443,469]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Biology.</emphasis>
This species inhabits tropical rain forest, tropical plantations, cloud forest, and oak forest located at altitudes from 
<quantity box="[731,906,484,510]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="18.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" unit="m" value="950.0" valueMax="1800.0" valueMin="100.0">100 to 1800 m</quantity>
. Months of collection in 
<collectingCountry box="[1201,1320,484,510]" name="Honduras" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Honduras</collectingCountry>
: May (22), June (229). Many specimens were collected on 
<taxonomicName box="[944,1131,524,549]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapotaceae" genus="Pouteria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sapota">
<emphasis box="[944,1131,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Pouteria sapota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName box="[1179,1314,524,550]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapotaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Sapotaceae</taxonomicName>
) at Yuscarán. Another species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" box="[663,838,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Macrodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[663,838,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Macrodactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[860,985,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Macrodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis box="[860,985,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">M. tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) was collected in the same place, time, and host.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1324,284,990]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,465,644,670]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Distribution</emphasis>
. Southeastern México to southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[920,1034,644,670]" name="Honduras" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Honduras</collectingCountry>
(13 ° 30'– 
<geoCoordinate box="[1159,1271,644,670]" degrees="15" direction="north" minutes="10" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" precision="925" value="15.166667">15° 10' N</geoCoordinate>
, 86° 10' – 
<geoCoordinate box="[322,443,684,710]" degrees="92" direction="west" minutes="30" orientation="longitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" precision="925" value="-92.5">92° 30' W</geoCoordinate>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1324,284,990]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,433,724,750]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was originally described with a large series of specimens from Sarstoon River (
<collectingCountry box="[462,543,764,790]" name="Belize" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Belize</collectingCountry>
); Dueñas, Coban (
<collectingCountry box="[759,893,764,790]" name="Guatemala" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
); 
<collectingRegion box="[912,1029,764,790]" country="Nicaragua" name="Chontales" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Chontales</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1045,1169,764,790]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
); and Volcan de Irazu (
<collectingCountry box="[374,509,804,830]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
). Arce­Pérez and 
<bibRefCitation author="Moron, M. A." box="[716,881,804,830]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" pagination="123 - 239" refId="ref6864" refString="Arce-Perez R. &amp; Moron, M. A. (2000) Taxonomia y distribucion de las especies de Macrodactylus Latreille (Coleoptera: Melolonthidae) de Mexico y America del Norte. Acta Zoologica Mexicana (n. s), 79, 123 - 239." type="journal article" year="2000">Morón (2000)</bibRefCitation>
added records from Tapachula, 
<collectingRegion country="Mexico" name="Chiapas" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Chiapas</collectingRegion>
, (
<collectingCountry box="[329,422,844,870]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">México</collectingCountry>
) and Palmar Viejo, 
<collectingRegion box="[669,853,844,870]" country="Guatemala" name="Quetzaltenango" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Quetzaltenango</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[871,1005,844,870]" name="Guatemala" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
). The variation in the 
<specimenCount pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="generic">251 specimens</specimenCount>
studied from 
<collectingCountry box="[548,662,884,910]" name="Honduras" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Honduras</collectingCountry>
was within the parameters of the specimens studied previously. The new records aid to link the distribution of this species between Chontales and 
<collectingCountry box="[264,394,964,990]" name="Guatemala" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
, across the chain of mountains in southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[945,1063,964,990]" name="Honduras" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Honduras</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
